The paper deals with developing a framework for efficient distributed multi-agent navigation, which involves obstacle avoidance. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed involves training a deep neural network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the navigation strategy of agents, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The method involves processing sensor measurements, which can be related to computer vision (cs.CV).
